How to Setup Virtual Environment in Ubuntu  Machine

# Make sure Python is installed on your machine 
1. python3 --version

# Install python3 Virtual Environment
2. sudo apt install python3-venv -y

# Install Venv Dependencies
3 pip install psutils

4.sudo apt update

# Create Virtual Environment
5. python3 -m venv myenv

# Activate Python Virtual Environment
6. source myenv/bin/activate

# Venv De-Activation
7. Deactivate
